# Deobfuscated Code & Explanation

## The Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
// Constants
const TAU = 6.283;          // 2π
const GOLDEN_RATIO = 1.618;
const SQRT_HALF = 0.707;    // √(1/2)

// Simulation configuration
const config = {
    gravity: 4000,           // Repulsion strength between nodes
    stiffion: 0.004,         // Spring stiffness (default)
    dampFriction: 0.92,      // Velocity damping per frame
    centering: 0.0003,       // Force pulling nodes toward center
    particleRate: 40,        // Max number of particles
    particleSpeed: 0.04,     // Particle speed decay factor
    deltaTime: 0.06          // Smoothing/lerp factor for camera
};

// ===== NODES (graph vertices) =====
const nodes = [
    { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "zeta",    label: "Zeta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// ===== EDGES (springs connecting nodes) =====
const edges = [
    { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "zeta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "beta",  b: "zeta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "beta",  b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera state (current and target)
let camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
let cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Ambient particles
let particles = [];
let frameCount = 0;

// Find a node by its ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// ===== PHYSICS SIMULATION =====
function updatePhysics() {
    // 1) Node-node REPULSION (inverse-square law, like charged particles)
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            let dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            let dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            let force = config.gravity / (dist * dist);
            let fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            let fy = (dy / dist) * force;

            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2) Spring ATTRACTION along edges (Hooke's law)
    for (let i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        let nodeA = findNode(edges[i].a);
        let nodeB = findNode(edges[i].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

        let dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        let dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        let dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        let displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
        let force = (edges[i].k || config.stiffion) * displacement;

        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3) Apply DAMPING, CENTERING force, and integrate velocity
    for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        // Damping (friction)
        nodes[i].vx *= config.dampFriction;
        nodes[i].vy *= config.dampFriction;

        // Centering force (pulls toward 400, 300)
        nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.centering;
        nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.centering;

        // Integrate position
        nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
        nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
    }
}

// ===== SPAWN AMBIENT PARTICLES =====
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.particleRate) return;

    let sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    let angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    let speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;

    particles.push({
        x: sourceNode.x,
        y: sourceNode.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * GOLDEN_RATIO * SQRT_HALF
    });
}

// ===== UPDATE PARTICLES =====
function updateParticles() {
    for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        let p = particles[i];
        p.vx *= 1 - config.particleSpeed * 0.125;
        p.vy *= 1 - config.particleSpeed * 0.125;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
            particles.splice(i, 1);
        }
    }
}

// ===== SMOOTH CAMERA =====
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.deltaTime;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.deltaTime;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.deltaTime;
}

// ===== MAIN LOOP =====
function tick() {
    updatePhysics();
    updateParticles();
    updateCamera();
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
    frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph layout simulation** — the kind commonly used to visualize network/graph data. Here's the breakdown:

### 🔵 Graph Structure
- **6 nodes** named after Greek letters (Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Zeta, Epsilon), each with a radius, position, and velocity
- **8 edges** (springs) connecting them, each with a rest length and spring constant

### ⚡ Physics Engine (runs every ~16ms)
The simulation applies three forces each frame:

| Force | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| **Repulsion** (inverse-square) | Pushes all nodes apart so they don't overlap — like electrically charged particles |
| **Spring attraction** (Hooke's law) | Pulls connected nodes toward their ideal distance (`rest` length) |
| **Centering gravity** | Gently pulls everything toward the center point (400, 300) |
| **Damping** (0.92× per frame) | Friction that gradually slows motion so the layout stabilizes |

### ✨ Particle System
- Every 3rd frame, a decorative particle spawns from a random node
- Particles drift outward with decaying velocity and eventually die (max age 800–2000 frames)
- Capped at 40 particles — purely cosmetic ambient effect

### 🎥 Smooth Camera
- Camera position and zoom lerp (linear interpolate) toward a target at 6% per frame, creating smooth panning/zooming

### In Summary
> **It's a headless force-directed graph physics engine with ambient particles and a smooth camera system** — likely the backend logic for an animated, interactive node-graph visualization (the rendering/drawing code is elsewhere).
